  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">WHO Participatory Video Project for the Decade of Healthy Ageing</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Activities: 
The primary audience reached by this project will be the core groups of older people who will participate in training workshops to become participatory video (PV)1 filmmakers in 6 communities (one per WHO region). They will be trained by facilitators in video-making techniques, and then design and shoot their own films among their peers and in their own communities. They will also be involved in the editing and screening processes.
Expected outputs: 
6 community-made films, one per country, each from a different community setting in one of WHO&apos;s regions (see site selection below). A compilation film will also be made, using excerpts from all 6 country-based films. 
The site videos will be screened (subject to the consent of the community film makers) firstly in their own communities, and thereafter at events to mark the formal launch of the Decade around the world, and any other relevant events in countries, regions and globally throughout the Decade. Films will be in the local languages with English subtitles.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to engage with older people, their family members, caregivers and communities, to amplify their diverse voices and foster their meaningful participation in the Decade of Healthy Ageing 2020-2030. Its outcome will be to offer a new opportunity to hear the voices and see the perspectives of a wide diversity of older people of all ages, functional abilities, settings and social categories.</narrative>
  </description>
